# <type>(<scope>): <summary>   (<= 72 chars, imperative mood)
#
# Body: explain WHAT and WHY (not how). Wrap at 72 chars.
#
# Footer: reference issues (Closes #123) and co-authors.
#
# Allowed types:
#   feat     A new feature
#   fix      A bug fix
#   perf     A performance improvement
#   refactor Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   docs     Documentation only
#   test     Adding or correcting tests
#   build    Build system or dependencies
#   ci       CI configuration
#   chore    Tooling / maintenance
#   revert   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Example:
#   feat(transport): add QUIC datagram path for native peers
#
#   Native peers negotiate RFC 9221 datagrams for video while keeping
#   reliable streams for input/files, avoiding head-of-line blocking.
#
#   Closes #42
#   Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
